name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: ha.failover-controller.graceful-fence.rpc-timeout.ms
description: Timeout that the FC waits for the old active to go to standby

name: dfs.namenode.decommission.backoff.monitor.pending.blocks.per.lock
description:
When loading blocks into the replication queue, release the namenode write
    lock after the defined number of blocks have been processed.

name: hadoop.security.kms.client.encrypted.key.cache.num.refill.threads
description:
Number of threads to use for refilling depleted EncryptedKeyVersion
    cache Queues

name: fs.s3a.socket.recv.buffer
description: Socket receive buffer hint to amazon connector. Represented in bytes.

name: dfs.client.deadnode.detection.probe.connection.timeout.ms
description: Connection timeout for probing dead node in milliseconds.

name: dfs.disk.balancer.max.disk.throughputInMBperSec
description:
Maximum disk bandwidth used by diskbalancer
      during read from a source disk. The unit is MB/sec.

name: mapreduce.task.combine.progress.records
description:
The number of records to process during combine output collection
   before sending a progress notification.

name: mapreduce.reduce.shuffle.fetch.retry.interval-ms
description:
Time of interval that fetcher retry to fetch again when some
  non-fatal failure happens because of some events like NM restart.
